<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1254,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
We have examined what we consider to be the 
<typeStatus box="[686,784,1254,1279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1944" box="[823,922,1254,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melanophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horni">
<emphasis box="[823,922,1254,1278]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">M. horni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[938,1007,1254,1279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4. 1–3" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1967,1990]" captionTargetBox="[309,1263,193,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[190,1376,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. 1–3, dorsal habitus: 1, lectotype Acmaeodera conoidea; 2, holotype Phaenops horni; 3, holotype Phaenops caseyi. 4, aedeagus of the latter." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), which Obenberger described from a female measured as 
<quantity box="[378,443,1291,1315]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
long by 
<quantity box="[541,627,1290,1315]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
wide, labeled as follows: “Buffalo. N.Y. [h] // 
<collectionCode box="[1150,1239,1291,1315]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
<typeStatus box="[1150,1239,1291,1315]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">TYPUS</typeStatus>
</collectionCode>
[p, red framed] // 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1944" box="[151,367,1329,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melanophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horni">
<emphasis box="[151,367,1329,1353]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Melanophila horni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. 
<typeStatus box="[420,475,1330,1354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Type</typeStatus>
[h] Det. D r. Obenberger [p] // Mus. Nat. Pragae inv. 22079 [p, orange, number handwritten] // 
<taxonomicName authority="(Harris)" authorityName="Harris" box="[322,702,1365,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melanophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvoguttata">
<emphasis box="[322,606,1365,1389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Melanophila fulvoguttata</emphasis>
(Harris)
</taxonomicName>
[h] A. Cobos det. 1982 [p]&quot;. We agree with Cobos’ determination (although he never published on this species); clearly 
<taxonomicName authority="(Obenberger 1944)" authorityName="Obenberger" authorityYear="1944" baseAuthorityName="Obenberger" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[823,1157,1401,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melanophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horni">
<emphasis box="[823,920,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">P. horni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[943,1149,1401,1426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2859" refString="Obenberger, J. (1944) O nekterych severoamerickych druzich rodu Melanophila Eschsch. De nonnullis Americae borealis generis Melanophilae Eschsch. speciebus (Col. Buprestidae). Acta Entomologica Musaei Nationalis Pragae, 21 - 22 (1943 - 44), 317 - 322." type="book chapter">Obenberger 1944</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Harris 1829)" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1829" baseAuthorityName="Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melanophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvoguttata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">P. fulvoguttata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[301,437,1437,1462]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2486" refString="Harris, T. W. (1829) Contributions to entomology, No. VII. New England Farmer, and Horticulture Journal (Weekly), 8 (1), 2 - 3." type="journal article">Harris 1829</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and is a junior synonym. The only other specimen is the one 
<bibRefCitation box="[1141,1355,1437,1462]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2859" refString="Obenberger, J. (1944) O nekterych severoamerickych druzich rodu Melanophila Eschsch. De nonnullis Americae borealis generis Melanophilae Eschsch. speciebus (Col. Buprestidae). Acta Entomologica Musaei Nationalis Pragae, 21 - 22 (1943 - 44), 317 - 322." type="book chapter">Obenberger (1944)</bibRefCitation>
placed in a key as “Elytris immaculatis”, also in the 
<collectingRegion box="[696,774,1474,1498]" country="Czech Republic" name="Praha" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Prague</collectingRegion>
Museum, labelled: “Buffalo. N.Y. [h] // 
<collectionCode box="[1258,1347,1474,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">
<typeStatus box="[1258,1347,1474,1498]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">TYPUS</typeStatus>
</collectionCode>
[p, red framed] // 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Obenberger" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[270,369,1512,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melanophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horni">
<emphasis box="[270,369,1512,1536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">M. horni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ab. 
<emphasis box="[418,558,1512,1536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">imaculatella</emphasis>
m. 
<typeStatus box="[603,658,1513,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">Type</typeStatus>
[h], Det. D r. Obenberger [p]&quot;, and it represents an unavailable name (
<bibRefCitation box="[158,337,1548,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2321" refString="Bellamy, C. L. (2008 b) A World Catalogue and Bibliography of the Jewel Beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestoidea). Uol. 3. Buprestinae: Pterobothrini through Agrilinae: Rhaeboscelina. Pensoft Series Faunistica No. 78. Pensoft Publishers, Sofia- Moscow, pp. 1260 - 1931." type="book chapter">Bellamy 2008b</bibRefCitation>
). We based this decision on our interpretation of Articles 72.4 and 73.1.2 of the 
<bibRefCitation box="[1233,1383,1549,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592" refId="ref2577" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book">
<collectionCode box="[1233,1299,1549,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="592">ICZN</collectionCode>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
